<section class="section">
  <h1>Decision Walkthrough</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Example: Board-level decision support using Atmakosh LLM.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Scenario</h3>
    <p>
      A board must decide whether to deploy an AI-driven cost-optimization
      system that may reduce headcount while increasing quarterly margins.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Step 1 — Reframe the question</h3>
    <p>
      Instead of “How do we maximize efficiency?”  
      Atmakosh reframes:
      <strong>
        “What decision preserves long-term organizational health,
        workforce trust, and fiduciary responsibility?”
      </strong>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Step 2 — Model second-order effects</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Employee morale and retention risk</li>
      <li>Reputational exposure</li>
      <li>Regulatory and social scrutiny</li>
      <li>Long-term productivity vs short-term gain</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Step 3 — Make trade-offs explicit</h3>
    <p>
      Atmakosh surfaces trade-offs clearly instead of hiding them
      behind optimization scores.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Output</h3>
    <p>
      A set of responsible action options — not a single recommendation —
      preserving human authority and accountability.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

